<p align="justify" class="Stil1">This script will configure you vsftpd server</p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1"><em>-GENERALLY-</em></p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1">&bull; <strong>File Unmask</strong>: Chmod of the new uploaded files <br>
&bull; <strong>Idle session timout</strong>: When do you want to disconnect an active ftp session<br>
&bull; <strong>Data connection timeout</strong>: When to disconnect a single upload/download file <br>
&bull; <strong>Welcome Banner Text</strong>: Your special text when connecting to the server<br>
&bull; <strong>FTP Username</strong>: Unique and unprivileged user<br>
</p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1"><em>- Anonymous FTP- </em></p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1">&bull; Here you can set what Anonmyous User can do or not can do.</p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1"><em>- Local User -</em></p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1">&bull; Here you can set what Local Users can do or not can do.</p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1"><em>- Log Infos-</em></p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1">&bull; Here you can set the Login Style of your ftp server.<br>
&bull; Optionally you can set webalizer logging fpr your ftp server</p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1"><em>- Miscellaneous - </em></p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1">&bull; <strong>Force dot files</strong>: Should we show dot files like .htacces in the ftp directory ?<br>
&bull; <strong>Listen address</strong>: On which IP address vsftpd will listen on<br>
&bull; <strong>Hide Files</strong>: Add files which will not be shown here. When using more than one file add like the following example: {folder,*.mp3,stats*}<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="Stil2">Note</span>: With more than one file user the {} method !!! Put the files between this two brakes. With just one file to hide don`t use {} !!!</p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1">&bull; <strong>Anon max rate in Bytes/sec</strong>: The speed Anonymous Users can up and/or download files.<br>
&bull; <strong>Local max rate in Bytes/sec</strong>: The speed Local Users can up and download files. </p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1"><em>-Manual entries-</em></p>
<p align="justify" class="Stil1">&bull; Here you can make changes directly on the vsftpd.conf file</p>
